WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:08.341
-[crickets chirping]
-[owl hooting]

2
00:00:08.425 --> 00:00:11.052
JINKEIEN

3
00:00:11.886 --> 00:00:14.222
[Miura. on TV]
Thank you all for being here tonight.

4
00:00:14.305 --> 00:00:18.393
As you all know.
I'm Takeshi Miura. the governor of Tokyo.

5
00:00:19.394 --> 00:00:21.855
I'd like to address
all my fellow citizens.

6
00:00:21.938 --> 00:00:23.440
First of all.

7
00:00:24.190 --> 00:00:27.235
I apologize for the late hour.

8
00:00:28.695 --> 00:00:32.490
Regarding the recent disturbances
involving the Human Vapor…

9
00:00:32.574 --> 00:00:33.742
How's he still alive?

10
00:00:33.825 --> 00:00:35.952
[Miura] …Fujita Fujikawa.
a video streamer…

11
00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:38.955
EMERGENCY PRESS CONFERENCE
FOURTH VICTIM

12
00:00:39.039 --> 00:00:41.708
…has been killed in a fire…

13
00:00:41.791 --> 00:00:43.084
POSSIBLE TERRORIST ATTACK

14
00:00:43.168 --> 00:00:44.753
…of unknown origin.

15
00:00:44.836 --> 00:00:47.255
The loss of any human life is tragic.

16
00:00:47.881 --> 00:00:50.008
While the investigation is ongoing…

17
00:00:50.091 --> 00:00:52.260
-[knock at door]
-[woman] Mr. Okamoto?

18
00:00:52.343 --> 00:00:53.219
Yeah?

19
00:00:53.303 --> 00:00:54.763
[woman] Sorry to disturb you.

20
00:00:55.263 --> 00:00:58.516
but dinner is ready.
if you'd please come to the dining room.

21
00:00:59.017 --> 00:01:00.810
[Kenji] Any chance we can eat in here?

22
00:01:01.352 --> 00:01:02.854
Oh. of course. I'll bring it in.

23
00:01:02.937 --> 00:01:05.815
-No. don't worry. I'll get it.
-[woman] Whatever you'd like.

24
00:01:05.899 --> 00:01:08.151
[Miura] …the Human Vapor
has not been acting alone.

25
00:01:08.234 --> 00:01:11.237
We now know the identity
of his accomplice.

26
00:01:11.738 --> 00:01:14.532
famed JNT reporter Kyoko Kono.

27
00:01:14.616 --> 00:01:17.327
-[somber music playing]
-A manhunt is underway.

28
00:01:17.827 --> 00:01:19.204
Her whereabouts are unknown.

29
00:01:19.287 --> 00:01:23.333
but we believe that she's hiding out
with the Human Vapor as we speak.

30
00:01:24.959 --> 00:01:27.712
According to
the Metropolitan Police Department…

31
00:01:27.796 --> 00:01:31.049
[PA system] …the possibility of a link
between Fujikawa and White Center

32
00:01:31.132 --> 00:01:32.175
is extremely low.

33
00:01:32.258 --> 00:01:35.220
They are not ruling out
any possibilities at this time.

34
00:01:35.303 --> 00:01:37.430
Of course. there will be more to come.

35
00:01:37.514 --> 00:01:39.140
[indistinct chattering nearby]

36
00:01:39.224 --> 00:01:41.810
[Miura] That said.
it seems increasingly likely

37
00:01:41.893 --> 00:01:46.773
that the series of murders carried out
by the Human Vapor and Kyoko Kono

38
00:01:46.856 --> 00:01:48.775
is completely random.

39
00:01:50.902 --> 00:01:53.571
I am asking my fellow citizens
to please stay home

40
00:01:53.655 --> 00:01:55.907
unless it is absolutely necessary.

41
00:01:55.990 --> 00:01:58.118
This is a very dangerous situation.

42
00:01:58.201 --> 00:02:00.286
If you must leave your home.

43
00:02:00.912 --> 00:02:04.374
I urge you to exercise extreme caution.

44
00:02:05.667 --> 00:02:06.918
Once again.

45
00:02:07.001 --> 00:02:08.753
I don't wish to cause alarm.

46
00:02:08.837 --> 00:02:12.924
but the possibility of an indiscriminate
terrorist act is significant.

47
00:02:13.007 --> 00:02:18.471
Please take every precaution you can
and refrain from any unnecessary outings.

48
00:02:18.555 --> 00:02:20.807
I cannot emphasize this enough.

49
00:02:22.142 --> 00:02:23.393
I can assure you.

50
00:02:23.476 --> 00:02:26.563
the authorities are doing
everything possible to keep you safe.

51
00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:32.402
[music fades out]

52
00:02:32.485 --> 00:02:35.780
[man on video] Times change.
and the notion of the strongest beings.

53
00:02:35.864 --> 00:02:39.993
you know. gods and great powers.
and all that crap. it changes.

54
00:02:40.076 --> 00:02:42.829
Think about where we were
in the 1800s till now…

55
00:02:55.175 --> 00:02:59.095
[Kaho. on video] Very exciting.
we got two applications come our way.

56
00:02:59.179 --> 00:03:01.723
from Yajima and Komoto Bad.

57
00:03:01.806 --> 00:03:03.683
[Fujita] Our two chosen ones!

58
00:03:03.766 --> 00:03:08.396
Fujita Occultic's Point!

59
00:03:10.023 --> 00:03:11.441
[Fujita screams]

60
00:03:11.524 --> 00:03:13.318
[Fujita screams again]

61
00:03:13.401 --> 00:03:14.235
Okay!

62
00:03:14.736 --> 00:03:17.113
That was two screams. [groans]

63
00:03:17.197 --> 00:03:19.449
But unfortunately. it's not enough!

64
00:03:19.532 --> 00:03:20.658
We need more blood!

65
00:03:20.742 --> 00:03:24.412
-More blood. more blood!
-[Kaho] They're gonna complain again.

66
00:03:24.913 --> 00:03:28.499
-Yajima. I have five words for you.
-[poignant music playing]

67
00:03:28.583 --> 00:03:31.002
[Fujita] Aim for the scream empire!

68
00:03:31.085 --> 00:03:33.880
-[Fujita screams]
-[Kaho] Oh my God. you need to stop!

69
00:03:33.963 --> 00:03:36.299
[Fujita chuckles] That was epic!

70
00:03:36.382 --> 00:03:38.176
Kaho… [Fujita laughs]

71
00:03:38.259 --> 00:03:40.303
-Kaho. come here.
-[Kaho] It's not happening.

72
00:03:40.386 --> 00:03:43.014
[Fujita] What's his name again?
The guy? Tomato. or. uh…

73
00:03:43.097 --> 00:03:44.057
[Kaho] Komoto Bad?

74
00:03:44.140 --> 00:03:46.559
[Fujita] Let's say thank you
to Komoto Bad. on camera.

75
00:03:46.643 --> 00:03:48.478
[Kaho] I told you. Not gonna happen.

76
00:03:48.561 --> 00:03:51.689
[Fujita] Let the world see
your beautiful face! Get over here!

77
00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:52.941
[Kaho] Not happening…

78
00:03:53.024 --> 00:03:54.901
JNT REPORTER KYOKO KONO WANTED!

79
00:03:54.984 --> 00:03:57.362
-[Fujita] Come on. my sister.
-[Kaho] Stop it!

80
00:03:57.445 --> 00:04:00.823
[Fujita] Everyone wants to see you.
It'll be fun. They're gonna love you.

81
00:04:00.907 --> 00:04:01.908
[Kaho] Give it up.

82
00:04:01.991 --> 00:04:03.576
-[Fujita] Please!
-[Kaho] Bye-bye.

83
00:04:04.202 --> 00:04:07.330
[newscaster] The Metropolitan Police
held a press conference

84
00:04:07.413 --> 00:04:10.124
in response to the recent murders
involving the Human Vapor.

85
00:04:10.208 --> 00:04:13.628
A new development has revealed
that famed JNT reporter Kyoko Kono

86
00:04:13.711 --> 00:04:15.046
has been working with the man

87
00:04:15.129 --> 00:04:17.090
and is now on a nationwide
most wanted list.

88
00:04:17.173 --> 00:04:20.051
-Kono is a member of JNT's Social Affairs…
-[Kaho exhales]

89
00:04:21.678 --> 00:04:23.137
[man] Excuse me. sir.

90
00:04:23.221 --> 00:04:26.432
I have the recent approval ratings
for the gubernatorial election.

91
00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:29.894
As you can see.
until about midway through the campaign.

92
00:04:29.978 --> 00:04:32.480
Kirishima had a considerable advantage.

93
00:04:33.606 --> 00:04:35.650
However. since the Human Vapor arrived…

94
00:04:35.733 --> 00:04:36.985
KIRISHIMA 36.2%
MIURA 35.8%

95
00:04:37.068 --> 00:04:39.821
…our approval ratings
have been climbing steadily.

96
00:04:41.489 --> 00:04:45.285
The more the public seems to panic.
the more I think

97
00:04:45.827 --> 00:04:49.163
they're inclined to choose stability
instead of rocking the boat.

98
00:04:52.750 --> 00:04:54.210
Having said that.

99
00:04:55.003 --> 00:04:58.339
there's still a sizable gap
between us and Kirishima.

100
00:05:00.508 --> 00:05:01.926
[Miura exhales]

101
00:05:18.109 --> 00:05:20.570
[dark. dramatic music playing]

102
00:05:56.898 --> 00:06:02.403
HUMAN VAPOR

103
00:06:02.487 --> 00:06:06.199
[muffled] Doo-doo-doo-doo! It's no good.
Doctor. Even Zaorik can't revive them!

104
00:06:06.282 --> 00:06:09.786
YOU HAVE A PRIVATE COMMENT
DADASHOW: PLEASE CONTACT 090689731

105
00:06:09.869 --> 00:06:11.287
[video playing over headphones]

106
00:06:11.371 --> 00:06:15.708
[Kaho. on video] Okay. as you can all see.
my brother's rampage is in full swing.

107
00:06:17.043 --> 00:06:19.796
When she gets this.
I think Kaho will contact us.

108
00:06:21.339 --> 00:06:22.215
All right.

109
00:06:24.759 --> 00:06:26.177
[Kyoko sighs deeply]

110
00:06:40.191 --> 00:06:42.402
[quiet. tense music playing]

111
00:06:56.040 --> 00:06:58.042
[exhales slowly]

112
00:07:03.881 --> 00:07:05.716
Something's been bothering me.

113
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:11.139
Is it okay if I ask you about it?

114
00:07:13.641 --> 00:07:14.600
[Kyoko] Mm.

115
00:07:17.937 --> 00:07:21.566
Why… were you there?

116
00:07:22.066 --> 00:07:23.734
At White Center?

117
00:07:26.154 --> 00:07:27.405
My mother…

118
00:07:30.324 --> 00:07:31.492
left me there.

119
00:07:34.036 --> 00:07:35.788
After my dad died.

120
00:07:37.206 --> 00:07:38.374
she…

121
00:07:39.333 --> 00:07:41.669
treated me like I was a burden.

122
00:07:44.839 --> 00:07:47.842
After a little while.
she moved in with another man.

123
00:07:49.343 --> 00:07:51.179
and handed me over.

124
00:07:53.639 --> 00:07:54.474
[Kenji sighs]

125
00:07:59.896 --> 00:08:01.689
When I ran away from White Center.

126
00:08:02.273 --> 00:08:04.525
I met Ren. Uncle Ren.

127
00:08:06.569 --> 00:08:09.906
Something about the bowl of ramen
he bought me that day…

128
00:08:09.989 --> 00:08:11.824
I don't know. I can't explain it.

129
00:08:18.789 --> 00:08:21.000
But it was the best thing I ever ate.

130
00:08:30.885 --> 00:08:34.347
And then he found out that I had no home.
no one to take care of me.

131
00:08:35.848 --> 00:08:37.517
[Ren] You're not alone. you know.

132
00:08:38.142 --> 00:08:40.520
When I was your age. I had nowhere to go.

133
00:08:41.604 --> 00:08:43.022
[soft music playing]

134
00:08:43.105 --> 00:08:46.317
Sometimes. when I look at you. Kyoko.

135
00:08:46.859 --> 00:08:49.028
it's like looking at myself back then.

136
00:08:52.782 --> 00:08:53.950
That's why…

137
00:08:57.036 --> 00:08:58.746
I couldn't just leave you.

138
00:09:00.248 --> 00:09:02.250
[Kyoko chuckles] Well…

139
00:09:03.292 --> 00:09:06.712
does that mean I can stay with you
for a little bit. Uncle Ren?

140
00:09:06.796 --> 00:09:08.047
[Ren] Whoa! Huh?

141
00:09:08.130 --> 00:09:09.298
[Ren chuckles]

142
00:09:10.216 --> 00:09:11.300
[bottle rattles]

143
00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:13.052
I found one! [gasps]

144
00:09:18.015 --> 00:09:20.393
Uncle Ren! Uncle Ren. I found one!

145
00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:22.103
[bottle rattles]

146
00:09:23.771 --> 00:09:25.356
Here. let's see your hand.

147
00:09:27.775 --> 00:09:28.859
[Kyoko] Oh! Oh!

148
00:09:28.943 --> 00:09:30.194
[Ren] Ha! Wow!

149
00:09:30.278 --> 00:09:33.531
-[Ren laughs] Ah! Oh. oh!
-[Kyoko] It's working!

150
00:09:33.614 --> 00:09:36.701
-[Ren] Oh wow! There it goes!
-[Kyoko] Whoa!

151
00:09:36.784 --> 00:09:38.828
-[Kyoko giggling]
-Great job!

152
00:09:38.911 --> 00:09:40.371
-Yay!
-Ha!

153
00:09:40.454 --> 00:09:41.664
[both laughing]

154
00:09:41.747 --> 00:09:44.375
[Ren and Kyoko singing in Japanese]
♪ …sets with the sun ♪

155
00:09:44.875 --> 00:09:46.460
[singing in English] ♪ Ellie ♪

156
00:09:46.544 --> 00:09:48.296
♪ My love ♪

157
00:09:48.379 --> 00:09:50.965
♪ So sweet… ♪

158
00:09:52.216 --> 00:09:54.594
[Kyoko] Those few months I spent with him.

159
00:09:55.344 --> 00:09:56.554
they were…

160
00:09:57.680 --> 00:10:00.099
the only happy childhood memories I have.

161
00:10:00.182 --> 00:10:02.852
Go right ahead and make a wish.
Let's hear it. Go on!

162
00:10:02.935 --> 00:10:04.312
["Ellie My Love" continues]

163
00:10:04.395 --> 00:10:06.063
Uh…

164
00:10:06.147 --> 00:10:08.816
-Come on. make a wish. you got it!
-Hmm…

165
00:10:08.899 --> 00:10:10.109
Tell me your wish. Kyoko.

166
00:10:10.192 --> 00:10:11.569
[shop owner] Say cheese!

167
00:10:16.991 --> 00:10:18.451
Over here…

168
00:10:19.910 --> 00:10:21.454
Ah. ah…

169
00:10:21.537 --> 00:10:22.747
Nice.

170
00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:26.167
[Ren chuckles]

171
00:10:29.337 --> 00:10:30.463
Oh.

172
00:10:31.172 --> 00:10:32.131
What's wrong?

173
00:10:33.049 --> 00:10:34.467
You don't like the picture?

174
00:10:36.302 --> 00:10:37.803
You wanna take another one?

175
00:10:39.972 --> 00:10:43.726
KYOKO AND REN

176
00:10:44.935 --> 00:10:46.312
Uncle Ren.

177
00:10:48.230 --> 00:10:49.065
[Ren] Hmm?

178
00:10:50.024 --> 00:10:50.858
Do…

179
00:10:51.859 --> 00:10:54.487
Do you wanna hear my wish?

180
00:10:54.570 --> 00:10:56.489
I'm ready to say it now.

181
00:10:56.572 --> 00:10:57.615
Of course.

182
00:11:01.160 --> 00:11:02.912
Into the mic.

183
00:11:08.209 --> 00:11:10.753
Okay. my wish is that you…

184
00:11:11.253 --> 00:11:12.546
That you…

185
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:13.964
[inaudible]

186
00:11:24.850 --> 00:11:26.977
[adult Kyoko] But it didn't last long.

187
00:11:35.986 --> 00:11:37.071
[owner] Welcome!

188
00:11:37.863 --> 00:11:39.490
[adult Kyoko] And right then.

189
00:11:40.157 --> 00:11:43.619
the door opened.
and my mom came looking for me with a man.

190
00:11:44.328 --> 00:11:46.038
Yasutoshi Mori.

191
00:11:46.914 --> 00:11:49.375
[tense music playing]

192
00:11:50.501 --> 00:11:51.502
[Kyoko's mother sighs]

193
00:11:52.294 --> 00:11:53.212
[Mori] So?

194
00:11:53.963 --> 00:11:54.839
What?

195
00:11:56.340 --> 00:11:57.633
Is that Kyoko?

196
00:12:00.136 --> 00:12:01.053
Yup.

197
00:12:02.680 --> 00:12:03.889
[Mori] Who's this guy?

198
00:12:05.683 --> 00:12:07.351
[exhales] No clue.

199
00:12:10.563 --> 00:12:11.772
[Mori] Oh…

200
00:12:11.856 --> 00:12:14.108
[tense music continues]

201
00:12:16.193 --> 00:12:19.822
[Mori] I guess introductions are in order.
Who might you be. exactly?

202
00:12:20.990 --> 00:12:21.824
Huh?

203
00:12:22.700 --> 00:12:25.536
[Ren] I'm her… guardian.

204
00:12:27.079 --> 00:12:28.664
[Mori and Kyoko's mother laugh]

205
00:12:28.748 --> 00:12:29.707
Guardian. huh?

206
00:12:30.624 --> 00:12:32.877
Well. I'm her mother. so…

207
00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:34.879
[scoffs] …what does she need
a guardian for?

208
00:12:35.463 --> 00:12:36.630
[sighs]

209
00:12:38.841 --> 00:12:40.009
Mother?

210
00:12:42.094 --> 00:12:44.180
Some mother you've been till now.

211
00:12:45.890 --> 00:12:48.476
You've been gone all this time.
You're not her mother!

212
00:12:50.144 --> 00:12:52.104
Hey. I gave birth to her.

213
00:12:52.605 --> 00:12:54.106
It was a pain in the ass!

214
00:12:55.107 --> 00:12:57.359
Now. now. now. Relax.

215
00:13:05.159 --> 00:13:06.535
[Mori] What. are you…

216
00:13:08.037 --> 00:13:09.371
getting your rocks off?

217
00:13:10.372 --> 00:13:11.999
You a perv? Huh?

218
00:13:12.792 --> 00:13:16.295
Protecting children
from sick predators like you

219
00:13:16.921 --> 00:13:17.880
is our job!

220
00:13:17.963 --> 00:13:19.673
[Ren grunting]

221
00:13:19.757 --> 00:13:21.175
[Kyoko] No! No!

222
00:13:21.258 --> 00:13:23.093
[mother] All right. shut up! Come with us!

223
00:13:23.636 --> 00:13:25.596
-Stop crying. We're going!
-No! No!

224
00:13:25.679 --> 00:13:26.680
[Ren grunts]

225
00:13:26.764 --> 00:13:28.265
Run. Kyoko!

226
00:13:29.558 --> 00:13:30.518
[Ren grunts]

227
00:13:31.602 --> 00:13:33.646
[Ren and Mori grunting]

228
00:13:33.729 --> 00:13:34.980
[owner] Stop! Stop!

229
00:13:35.064 --> 00:13:38.025
Come on. Kyoko. let's go.
Let's not get into more trouble.

230
00:13:38.776 --> 00:13:40.861
Come on! Come here. Kyoko!

231
00:13:42.863 --> 00:13:44.240
-[Ren] Run!
-[Mori grunts]

232
00:13:44.323 --> 00:13:46.075
[Mori panting]

233
00:13:46.158 --> 00:13:48.577
[mother] Hurry up
and kill this guy already!

234
00:13:48.661 --> 00:13:50.788
[owner's wife] Hello? I need the police.

235
00:13:50.871 --> 00:13:52.832
I'm at Bunko Ramen in Tateishi!

236
00:13:52.915 --> 00:13:55.668
-[Mori and Ren grunting]
-[objects crashing]

237
00:13:55.751 --> 00:13:57.837
THEFT
DIVISION 2

238
00:13:57.920 --> 00:14:02.758
Listen. I was entrusted with this child
by her mother.

239
00:14:02.842 --> 00:14:06.136
-[Ren] They're bad people. Ask her.
-[Mori] That pervert kidnapped her.

240
00:14:06.220 --> 00:14:07.263
[mother] He did.

241
00:14:07.763 --> 00:14:10.432
He tried to do awful things
to my daughter.

242
00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:12.017
[Ren] I didn't touch her.

243
00:14:13.227 --> 00:14:14.353
[mother] Hey. pervert!

244
00:14:14.436 --> 00:14:16.897
Don't try and lie. We got you!

245
00:14:17.606 --> 00:14:18.524
[sighs]

246
00:14:19.567 --> 00:14:21.902
Uncle Ren didn't do anything wrong.

247
00:14:21.986 --> 00:14:23.320
Shut up!

248
00:14:24.321 --> 00:14:26.866
It's that kind of lip
that got you sent to the center!

249
00:14:26.949 --> 00:14:29.618
-[Ren] Hey!
-[detective 1] Stop it! Sit down!

250
00:14:29.702 --> 00:14:31.370
[detective 2] What's the problem?

251
00:14:31.453 --> 00:14:33.038
Oh. Okamoto.

252
00:14:35.791 --> 00:14:37.042
Oh. Mori.

253
00:14:38.043 --> 00:14:41.088
-What the hell d'you do now? Huh?
-[chuckles] Mr. Okamoto.

254
00:14:41.171 --> 00:14:42.882
-It's a misunderstanding.
-Sit.

255
00:14:44.466 --> 00:14:46.844
[detective 3] Is there anyone
who can verify your identity?

256
00:14:46.927 --> 00:14:48.012
[Shinya] What did he do?

257
00:14:48.929 --> 00:14:51.557
[detective 1] Nothing.
these two were the victims.

258
00:14:51.640 --> 00:14:52.808
-Ren Tsutsumida.
-I see.

259
00:14:52.892 --> 00:14:54.768
[detective 3] That your real name?

260
00:14:58.147 --> 00:15:00.482
-What about work? You got a job?
-[Mori] Uh…

261
00:15:01.734 --> 00:15:04.320
Well. I could tell you I was working.

262
00:15:06.697 --> 00:15:09.325
You can call and verify me
with White Center.

263
00:15:09.825 --> 00:15:10.951
White Center?

264
00:15:12.453 --> 00:15:15.748
Oh. Seems to be
a kinda social welfare facility

265
00:15:15.831 --> 00:15:17.416
supported by the government.

266
00:15:19.627 --> 00:15:21.337
Oh. this must be him.

267
00:15:21.420 --> 00:15:23.589
Uh… I'm sorry to keep you waiting.

268
00:15:23.672 --> 00:15:25.633
Um. hello.
I'm the director of White Center.

269
00:15:25.716 --> 00:15:28.177
-Hiroki Obata.
-[detective 1] Thanks for coming.

270
00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:31.472
[Obata] I'm so sorry
about all the. um. trouble today.

271
00:15:31.555 --> 00:15:33.557
[mysterious music playing]

272
00:15:36.518 --> 00:15:38.145
[Shinya] What are you looking at?

273
00:15:41.482 --> 00:15:43.067
You wanna see something cool?

274
00:15:45.319 --> 00:15:47.321
[music fades out]

275
00:15:57.039 --> 00:15:57.873
Hmm?

276
00:16:03.796 --> 00:16:04.838
You wanna try?

277
00:16:05.506 --> 00:16:06.423
Go on.

278
00:16:08.050 --> 00:16:09.259
[Shinya chuckles]

279
00:16:16.558 --> 00:16:20.020
You know. you can tell me
if that tall man did something to you.

280
00:16:21.313 --> 00:16:23.107
Did he try to touch you or anything?

281
00:16:25.401 --> 00:16:27.820
Maybe yell at you. or did he hit you?

282
00:16:31.115 --> 00:16:33.659
Uncle Ren would never do
something like that.

283
00:16:34.368 --> 00:16:35.995
[chuckles softly] Okay.

284
00:16:37.579 --> 00:16:38.747
And your mom?

285
00:16:39.915 --> 00:16:41.458
Has she ever hit you maybe?

286
00:16:48.132 --> 00:16:50.009
Do you wanna go back to White Center?

287
00:16:53.345 --> 00:16:55.222
[Mori] Mr. Okamoto. please.

288
00:16:55.305 --> 00:16:59.018
We already settled this whole thing
upstairs. We're done.

289
00:16:59.560 --> 00:17:02.604
Kyoko. we've talked it all out. okay?

290
00:17:02.688 --> 00:17:03.772
We think

291
00:17:04.273 --> 00:17:06.525
it's best that you go home with Uncle Ren.

292
00:17:07.359 --> 00:17:08.736
-Really?
-Yeah.

293
00:17:12.072 --> 00:17:13.240
-[Kyoko sighs]
-[Ren] Oh!

294
00:17:17.244 --> 00:17:20.164
I assume we can count on you
to keep your promise?

295
00:17:24.918 --> 00:17:27.755
All right then. You take care.

296
00:17:28.630 --> 00:17:29.548
Bye-bye.

297
00:17:31.133 --> 00:17:33.093
Hey. whoa. wait up. will ya?

298
00:17:34.178 --> 00:17:35.429
I'm starving!

299
00:17:35.512 --> 00:17:37.389
[Mori] It's your brat's fault.

300
00:17:37.473 --> 00:17:40.809
[mother] Don't be mad at me.
I'll buy lunch. okay? I'm sorry…

301
00:17:41.310 --> 00:17:42.144
Thank you.

302
00:17:45.481 --> 00:17:47.566
[emotional music playing]

303
00:17:52.279 --> 00:17:53.614
[Kenji] So…

304
00:17:54.740 --> 00:17:56.241
That detective…

305
00:17:58.202 --> 00:18:00.120
[Kyoko] I don't remember his name.

306
00:18:00.829 --> 00:18:02.956
But he was a really good person.

307
00:18:10.255 --> 00:18:11.924
That was probably…

308
00:18:16.095 --> 00:18:17.221
my father.

309
00:18:18.222 --> 00:18:19.139
Really?

310
00:18:20.432 --> 00:18:21.767
[Kenji exhales]

311
00:18:23.268 --> 00:18:24.353
Here.

312
00:18:26.355 --> 00:18:27.481
Check it out.

313
00:18:28.857 --> 00:18:30.651
My dad's old notebook.

314
00:18:32.611 --> 00:18:33.612
[Kenji sighs]

315
00:18:35.531 --> 00:18:37.699
He was looking into White Center.

316
00:18:39.701 --> 00:18:41.620
Till he was killed in an accident.

317
00:19:10.315 --> 00:19:14.236
I'LL BE BACK TOMORROW.
WAIT FOR ME UNTIL THEN. OKAY?

318
00:19:14.319 --> 00:19:16.572
[dark. tense music playing]

319
00:19:17.156 --> 00:19:18.532
Uncle Ren!

320
00:19:20.033 --> 00:19:21.910
[panting]

321
00:19:22.661 --> 00:19:25.622
Hello? Mister? Hello? Are you there?

322
00:19:26.165 --> 00:19:28.125
-[owner] What's wrong?
-I can't find Uncle Ren!

323
00:19:28.208 --> 00:19:30.961
Huh? Uh. where was it again?
Uh. where the meteorite landed…

324
00:19:31.044 --> 00:19:33.380
He said he was going
to help the cleanup crew.

325
00:19:33.463 --> 00:19:34.506
Where is that?

326
00:19:42.639 --> 00:19:44.683
We can't go past here. unfortunately.

327
00:19:45.976 --> 00:19:48.020
No. no. stop! It's dangerous!

328
00:19:48.520 --> 00:19:50.772
Kyoko! You can't go in there!

329
00:19:50.856 --> 00:19:52.941
[grunts] Come back here!

330
00:19:53.025 --> 00:19:53.942
[groans]

331
00:19:54.026 --> 00:19:56.028
[dark. tense music continues]

332
00:20:00.908 --> 00:20:03.285
[music intensifies]

333
00:20:03.368 --> 00:20:05.495
[Ren screaming in pain]

334
00:20:06.955 --> 00:20:08.290
Uncle Ren!

335
00:20:08.373 --> 00:20:10.876
-[Ren screaming] Help me!
-[Kyoko] Uncle Ren!

336
00:20:11.627 --> 00:20:12.836
Uncle Ren!

337
00:20:12.920 --> 00:20:15.130
-[Mori] Stay back! Get the hell off me!
-Help me!

338
00:20:15.214 --> 00:20:17.591
[Ren choking. groaning]

339
00:20:20.969 --> 00:20:23.972
[wailing] No!

340
00:20:25.557 --> 00:20:27.851
[Ren screaming in pain]

341
00:20:27.935 --> 00:20:30.312
[Kyoko shrieking]

342
00:20:31.939 --> 00:20:34.608
[sobbing] Uncle Ren!

343
00:20:42.282 --> 00:20:45.160
[screaming] No! Uncle Ren!

344
00:20:46.411 --> 00:20:48.538
[explosion]

345
00:20:49.498 --> 00:20:51.500
[music fades out]

346
00:20:52.459 --> 00:20:53.627
[Kyoko] After that…

347
00:20:55.629 --> 00:20:57.381
I never saw him again.

348
00:20:59.049 --> 00:21:00.217
[Kenji sighs]

349
00:21:02.135 --> 00:21:03.220
[exhales]

350
00:21:11.478 --> 00:21:13.563
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you before.

351
00:21:29.621 --> 00:21:30.622
[Kenji] No.

352
00:21:40.507 --> 00:21:41.758
I understand.

353
00:21:42.259 --> 00:21:43.510
Thank you.

354
00:21:46.305 --> 00:21:48.056
I'm glad you told me now.

355
00:22:08.535 --> 00:22:10.662
[birds singing outside]

356
00:22:24.259 --> 00:22:26.928
[vehicle approaching]

357
00:22:35.312 --> 00:22:37.105
[foreboding music playing]

358
00:22:48.283 --> 00:22:49.451
It's this one.

359
00:22:53.038 --> 00:22:56.083
Mr. Okamoto? Do you mind if I come in?

360
00:22:56.166 --> 00:22:58.335
[foreboding music building]

361
00:22:59.086 --> 00:23:00.379
[knocking at door]

362
00:23:00.462 --> 00:23:01.963
[woman] Mr. Okamoto?

363
00:23:03.256 --> 00:23:05.467
Open the door. It's the police.

364
00:23:08.720 --> 00:23:11.223
-Mr. Okamoto?
-He's not here.

365
00:23:11.723 --> 00:23:14.643
I can promise you
he was in here last night.

366
00:23:15.602 --> 00:23:17.604
[music becomes melancholic]

367
00:23:35.789 --> 00:23:37.624
[phone vibrating]

368
00:23:37.707 --> 00:23:39.709
[phone continues vibrating]

369
00:23:41.253 --> 00:23:44.172
PAY PHONE

370
00:23:49.886 --> 00:23:50.971
Yes. hello?

371
00:23:52.097 --> 00:23:53.140
[Kaho] Hello.

372
00:23:54.099 --> 00:23:55.016
[Kyoko] Kaho?

373
00:23:56.601 --> 00:23:57.436
Yeah.

374
00:24:00.147 --> 00:24:01.982
How are you? Are you okay?

375
00:24:03.316 --> 00:24:04.359
[Kyoko] Yeah.

376
00:24:06.194 --> 00:24:07.446
Kaho. listen.

377
00:24:08.363 --> 00:24:10.157
I'm so sorry

378
00:24:11.783 --> 00:24:12.993
about everything.

379
00:24:13.076 --> 00:24:14.661
I want you to know that.

380
00:24:16.746 --> 00:24:19.207
Governor Miura was the one
who killed Fujita.

381
00:24:21.293 --> 00:24:24.045
He found out how to control
the Human Vapor.

382
00:24:25.797 --> 00:24:27.966
and then he ordered him to kill us.

383
00:24:28.925 --> 00:24:31.344
Well. then… he's coming for you.

384
00:24:31.428 --> 00:24:33.054
We need to meet up right now.

385
00:24:33.138 --> 00:24:34.181
Okay?

386
00:24:34.890 --> 00:24:35.724
Okay.

387
00:24:36.516 --> 00:24:38.101
[car horn beeps]

388
00:24:45.275 --> 00:24:47.277
[music fades out]

389
00:24:49.154 --> 00:24:50.405
Kyoko.

390
00:24:52.073 --> 00:24:53.158
When did you…

391
00:24:55.160 --> 00:24:57.329
realize that Ren was the Human Vapor?

392
00:24:59.623 --> 00:25:01.208
About six years ago.

393
00:25:02.667 --> 00:25:05.545
Back when JNT was still in Shinagawa.

394
00:25:06.463 --> 00:25:09.799
-[man] We'll be counting on you. Ms. Fuji.
-[woman] Yes. sir.

395
00:25:09.883 --> 00:25:12.385
So up next. we have The Lost Time.

396
00:25:12.469 --> 00:25:15.138
Kataoka's feeling
a little under the weather today.

397
00:25:15.639 --> 00:25:16.973
Can someone cover?

398
00:25:17.057 --> 00:25:18.683
[man 2] Hmm. I would.

399
00:25:18.767 --> 00:25:21.561
but I gotta get over
to the Iwaki fishing port.

400
00:25:22.103 --> 00:25:23.855
VACANT LOTS ARE A PROBLEM
FOR NEIGHBORS

401
00:25:23.939 --> 00:25:26.233
[Kyoko] I was looking over the plans
during a meeting…

402
00:25:26.316 --> 00:25:27.317
[pen clatters]

403
00:25:32.697 --> 00:25:33.657
I can make it work.

404
00:25:34.157 --> 00:25:37.661
[Kyoko now] It was abandoned at the time.
but there was no doubt in my mind.

405
00:25:37.744 --> 00:25:40.163
It was the place
Uncle Ren and I used to live.

406
00:25:40.247 --> 00:25:42.249
[gentle music playing]

407
00:25:47.671 --> 00:25:49.881
No one had rented the warehouse.

408
00:25:50.465 --> 00:25:53.468
and it had been abandoned
for over 20 years.

409
00:26:15.240 --> 00:26:16.491
[chuckles softly]

410
00:26:29.879 --> 00:26:31.631
[music fades out]

411
00:26:31.715 --> 00:26:34.259
-[rattling]
-[wind whistling faintly]

412
00:26:34.342 --> 00:26:40.557
RECORDING

413
00:26:47.772 --> 00:26:49.774
[haunting music playing]

414
00:27:03.079 --> 00:27:05.081
[mysterious music playing]

415
00:27:14.215 --> 00:27:16.217
[Kyoko breathing nervously]

416
00:27:30.523 --> 00:27:32.609
When I went down to the basement.

417
00:27:32.692 --> 00:27:36.905
I saw that Uncle Ren had become
this… kind of statue.

418
00:27:37.405 --> 00:27:38.531
I can't explain it.

419
00:27:38.615 --> 00:27:42.827
but maybe the parts of his body
that had turned to gas had somehow

420
00:27:43.745 --> 00:27:45.872
been pulled back together.

421
00:27:51.294 --> 00:27:52.712
Uncle Ren?

422
00:27:55.006 --> 00:27:57.967
I thought that maybe
he'd finally found peace.

423
00:27:58.718 --> 00:28:01.304
I wanted to ask him. talk to him.

424
00:28:01.388 --> 00:28:03.098
but he never answered.

425
00:28:09.771 --> 00:28:12.607
I immediately bought the warehouse.
Cleaned it up.

426
00:28:12.691 --> 00:28:15.193
Every few months.
I would go back and visit.

427
00:28:17.737 --> 00:28:19.489
[Kyoko inhales. then blows softly]

428
00:28:19.572 --> 00:28:21.157
ELLIE MY LOVE
SOUTHERN ALL STARS

429
00:28:21.241 --> 00:28:22.617
And it was after that

430
00:28:24.411 --> 00:28:25.745
that I met you.

431
00:28:28.331 --> 00:28:29.791
[truck horn beeps]

432
00:28:31.084 --> 00:28:33.712
[soft music playing]

433
00:28:45.557 --> 00:28:47.851
For the first time in a long time.

434
00:28:49.644 --> 00:28:51.980
I thought I might be able to…

435
00:28:53.356 --> 00:28:57.902
forget about everything from the past
and live happily.

436
00:29:07.078 --> 00:29:08.455
-Here we go.
-[Kenji groans]

437
00:29:08.538 --> 00:29:09.497
[Kyoko sighs]

438
00:29:10.790 --> 00:29:12.208
[Kenji moans]

439
00:29:13.752 --> 00:29:16.212
Bastard's never gonna face the music.

440
00:29:17.505 --> 00:29:20.967
He's just gonna do it again and again
and keep getting away with it.

441
00:29:22.177 --> 00:29:25.555
He's gonna learn from this time
and get smarter.

442
00:29:40.111 --> 00:29:41.738
[intriguing music playing]

443
00:30:15.605 --> 00:30:17.440
[Kenji breathing softly]

444
00:30:27.283 --> 00:30:29.619
[Kyoko breathing heavily]

445
00:30:36.751 --> 00:30:40.296
ELLIE MY LOVE
SOUTHERN ALL STARS

446
00:30:40.380 --> 00:30:42.757
["Ellie My Love"
by Southern All Stars playing]

447
00:30:42.841 --> 00:30:43.967
Uncle Ren.

448
00:30:45.552 --> 00:30:46.636
I…

449
00:30:51.724 --> 00:30:54.018
I found someone I really care about.

450
00:30:58.648 --> 00:31:00.692
And I also found someone else.

451
00:31:01.776 --> 00:31:02.819
[sniffs]

452
00:31:04.612 --> 00:31:06.948
The guy who did this to you.

453
00:31:13.329 --> 00:31:14.247
I…

454
00:31:17.500 --> 00:31:20.378
I don't know what to do.
Do I go after him?

455
00:31:24.132 --> 00:31:26.342
[sniffs] What should I do?

456
00:31:27.677 --> 00:31:28.845
Uncle Ren…

457
00:31:29.888 --> 00:31:31.431
♪ Ellie ♪

458
00:31:31.514 --> 00:31:32.974
♪ My love ♪

459
00:31:33.057 --> 00:31:36.019
♪ So sweet… ♪

460
00:31:48.656 --> 00:31:50.283
Is that really you?

461
00:31:57.123 --> 00:31:58.917
♪ Ellie ♪

462
00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:00.668
♪ My love… ♪

463
00:32:01.294 --> 00:32:03.046
[crying] What's wrong with you?

464
00:32:04.213 --> 00:32:05.924
Please talk to me.

465
00:32:06.007 --> 00:32:07.425
♪ My love ♪

466
00:32:07.508 --> 00:32:10.720
♪ So sweet… ♪

467
00:32:22.440 --> 00:32:24.442
[Human Vapor] Greetings. listener.

468
00:32:25.443 --> 00:32:27.153
Go right ahead

469
00:32:27.820 --> 00:32:29.572
and make a wish.

470
00:32:45.171 --> 00:32:46.589
[sighs sadly]

471
00:32:52.178 --> 00:32:54.263
[Kyoko crying]

472
00:32:56.724 --> 00:32:57.976
[Kenji] So…

473
00:32:59.435 --> 00:33:00.728
what did you wish for?

474
00:33:04.941 --> 00:33:07.193
[tense music playing]

475
00:33:07.276 --> 00:33:09.779
[Mori] I found a good spot.
Let's go there next time.

476
00:33:09.862 --> 00:33:11.197
[man 1] Yeah. I'd love that.

477
00:33:11.280 --> 00:33:14.033
[man 2] Look forward to it.
Let's put something on the books.

478
00:33:15.243 --> 00:33:17.787
[Kyoko] Excuse me! Excuse me!
Yasutoshi Mori?

479
00:33:18.621 --> 00:33:19.789
Who the hell are you?

480
00:33:19.872 --> 00:33:21.916
You were recently questioned by the police

481
00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:24.252
about a high-school girl
who died of an overdose.

482
00:33:24.335 --> 00:33:27.422
-Care to comment on that?
-Hey. get that camera out of my face.

483
00:33:27.505 --> 00:33:28.923
Get that camera off me.

484
00:33:29.007 --> 00:33:30.842
Seeing as there are shareholders here.

485
00:33:30.925 --> 00:33:33.511
wouldn't it be a good idea
to prove your innocence. sir?

486
00:33:33.594 --> 00:33:35.388
I'm not guilty of anything.

487
00:33:35.471 --> 00:33:40.226
Then why refuse to provide your cell phone
to the police during questioning?

488
00:33:40.810 --> 00:33:42.979
[Mori] Speaking of police.
I'm calling them now.

489
00:33:43.062 --> 00:33:44.939
Hey! Get them out of here. would you?

490
00:33:45.023 --> 00:33:46.858
[Kyoko] Nice phone. Mr. Mori. Is it new?

491
00:33:47.358 --> 00:33:50.945
You got rid of your old phone. didn't you.
so they couldn't see what was there?

492
00:33:51.571 --> 00:33:54.115
Don't you feel guilty at all. sir?
She was a young girl!

493
00:33:54.198 --> 00:33:55.658
[guard] Leave quietly.

494
00:33:56.159 --> 00:33:58.202
Come on. move away. please! Come on.

495
00:33:58.286 --> 00:34:00.538
-Hey. stop. Stop!
-Answer me. sir!

496
00:34:00.621 --> 00:34:02.623
[music fades out]

497
00:34:03.875 --> 00:34:06.002
[Kyoko breathing heavily]

498
00:34:20.850 --> 00:34:23.728
-[guard] I told you to stop filming.
-Don't touch my camera!

499
00:34:30.526 --> 00:34:32.737
I could give a comment. you know.

500
00:34:32.820 --> 00:34:34.822
[sinister music playing]

501
00:34:46.501 --> 00:34:47.543
[Mori sighs]

502
00:34:47.627 --> 00:34:49.420
Nope. not to you.

503
00:34:49.504 --> 00:34:51.130
Sorry. sweet cheeks.

504
00:34:51.214 --> 00:34:52.673
[Mori laughs]

505
00:34:53.758 --> 00:34:55.843
[footsteps receding]

506
00:35:03.684 --> 00:35:05.019
Hey. Uncle Ren.

507
00:35:06.646 --> 00:35:07.772
I know

508
00:35:08.898 --> 00:35:10.566
what I wanna wish for.

509
00:35:13.069 --> 00:35:14.362
I wish…

510
00:35:16.572 --> 00:35:19.158
to kill the man
who took you away back then.

511
00:35:19.659 --> 00:35:21.786
The man with the snake tattoo.

512
00:35:25.164 --> 00:35:27.625
I want to kill Yasutoshi Mori.

513
00:35:32.713 --> 00:35:33.881
Please.

514
00:35:35.591 --> 00:35:36.717
Uncle Ren.

515
00:35:46.894 --> 00:35:49.397
[swing music playing]

516
00:35:49.480 --> 00:35:52.942
♪ I knew it when you smiled at me ♪

517
00:35:53.484 --> 00:35:55.945
♪ That in my arms you soon would be… ♪

518
00:35:56.028 --> 00:35:57.530
[sniffs]

519
00:35:57.613 --> 00:36:00.783
♪ Dancing all night long… ♪

520
00:36:00.867 --> 00:36:02.618
[grunts. sniffs]

521
00:36:02.702 --> 00:36:04.162
[doorbell rings]

522
00:36:04.245 --> 00:36:07.248
♪ It was a hot and steamy night ♪

523
00:36:07.999 --> 00:36:09.542
♪ Music played… ♪

524
00:36:09.625 --> 00:36:11.377
[doorbell rings]

525
00:36:11.460 --> 00:36:14.964
♪ As we began to carry on ♪

526
00:36:15.047 --> 00:36:18.092
♪ Dancing all night long ♪

527
00:36:18.801 --> 00:36:22.013
-♪ Cha-cha-cha. mambo too ♪
-[Mori singing along]

528
00:36:22.096 --> 00:36:23.890
♪ The rhythm was… ♪

529
00:36:27.894 --> 00:36:28.895
[scoffs]

530
00:36:29.979 --> 00:36:31.314
I made myself clear.

531
00:36:31.397 --> 00:36:33.107
Not you.

532
00:36:33.191 --> 00:36:34.358
Will you hold on?

533
00:36:35.109 --> 00:36:38.988
-I need to talk to you a minute.
-I've got nothing to say to you!

534
00:36:39.071 --> 00:36:40.990
Now. get lost!

535
00:36:41.073 --> 00:36:41.991
[Mori chokes]

536
00:36:42.533 --> 00:36:44.160
[tense music playing]

537
00:36:44.243 --> 00:36:45.995
[Mori choking]

538
00:36:46.954 --> 00:36:48.539
[Mori gurgling. grunting]

539
00:36:51.709 --> 00:36:53.628
[air whooshing]

540
00:36:54.420 --> 00:36:56.464
What's happening? What is this?

541
00:36:56.964 --> 00:36:58.549
[yells] Let go!

542
00:37:00.551 --> 00:37:03.638
[Mori] Stop! Stop. please! Please! Stop!

543
00:37:05.139 --> 00:37:06.182
[Mori choking]

544
00:37:06.891 --> 00:37:09.310
Let me go! Please. stop!

545
00:37:16.817 --> 00:37:21.197
[choking] I'm sorry. okay?
I'll tell you anything you want. please!

546
00:37:21.280 --> 00:37:23.616
Anything! Please. stop!

547
00:37:24.659 --> 00:37:27.453
[choking]

548
00:37:27.536 --> 00:37:29.121
[gasping]

549
00:37:29.705 --> 00:37:34.126
When the meteorite crashed 27 years ago.
who was in charge of the cleanup?

550
00:37:34.210 --> 00:37:35.419
[Mori coughs. gasps]

551
00:37:35.503 --> 00:37:37.546
[Mori] Wait. what? Uh…

552
00:37:37.630 --> 00:37:39.548
[gasping]

553
00:37:39.632 --> 00:37:44.095
Look. the boss just ordered me to help out
with some work at White Center!

554
00:37:44.679 --> 00:37:48.057
"The boss"? Does that mean yakuza?

555
00:37:48.140 --> 00:37:49.850
[gasping] Yeah.

556
00:37:51.227 --> 00:37:52.395
Otomo…

557
00:37:52.895 --> 00:37:53.771
[grunts]

558
00:37:54.272 --> 00:37:55.940
Otomo Saburo.

559
00:37:59.402 --> 00:38:01.612
So yakuza was involved with White Center?

560
00:38:03.114 --> 00:38:04.657
Tell me how they were connected.

561
00:38:04.740 --> 00:38:06.409
I swear. I don't know!

562
00:38:06.951 --> 00:38:09.578
I just transported people
to the professor.

563
00:38:09.662 --> 00:38:11.664
[Kyoko] Professor? What professor?

564
00:38:11.747 --> 00:38:12.915
[Mori] Sano…

565
00:38:13.666 --> 00:38:16.419
I think his name is Kyugo Sano.

566
00:38:17.169 --> 00:38:19.380
He did an interview on the TV
the other day.

567
00:38:19.463 --> 00:38:22.258
pretending to be
some kind of upstanding citizen.

568
00:38:22.341 --> 00:38:24.677
[Kyoko] Saburo Otomo. Kyugo Sano…

569
00:38:25.261 --> 00:38:27.263
[Mori gasping. groaning]

570
00:38:28.264 --> 00:38:29.098
Anybody else?

571
00:38:30.349 --> 00:38:33.352
I swear to you. that's all I know.

572
00:38:34.061 --> 00:38:37.523
Wait. maybe…
there was someone on the police force.

573
00:38:38.816 --> 00:38:39.817
On the police force?

574
00:38:39.900 --> 00:38:41.986
-[Mori gasping]
-Give me his name.

575
00:38:42.069 --> 00:38:44.322
I told you. I don't know!

576
00:38:44.822 --> 00:38:47.658
Please. let me go!
I told you everything I could!

577
00:38:48.409 --> 00:38:51.329
-Let me down!
-I just have one more point.

578
00:38:53.539 --> 00:38:55.624
Do you recognize the man in front of you?

579
00:38:57.126 --> 00:38:59.045
Does his face ring a bell?

580
00:39:07.887 --> 00:39:09.430
No. Should it?

581
00:39:11.515 --> 00:39:13.309
What? Should I know?

582
00:39:14.018 --> 00:39:15.186
Who is he. then?

583
00:39:17.813 --> 00:39:18.856
Okay.

584
00:39:19.899 --> 00:39:20.941
Hey. whoa.

585
00:39:21.525 --> 00:39:23.652
You… You said if I told you everything…

586
00:39:23.736 --> 00:39:24.612
Hey!

587
00:39:24.695 --> 00:39:26.197
[whooshing]

588
00:39:26.781 --> 00:39:29.617
[Mori] Help! Someone. help me! Please!

589
00:39:31.744 --> 00:39:33.579
Please! [choking]

590
00:39:33.662 --> 00:39:35.748
[Kyoko] That's what he said to you too.

591
00:39:35.831 --> 00:39:37.583
-[Mori chokes]
-[loud thud]

592
00:39:41.587 --> 00:39:43.589
[whooshing softens]

593
00:40:01.565 --> 00:40:03.567
[silence]

594
00:40:09.990 --> 00:40:12.159
[melancholy music playing]

595
00:40:12.243 --> 00:40:14.245
[Kyoko grunting]

596
00:40:18.958 --> 00:40:21.210
[sobbing]

597
00:40:25.840 --> 00:40:28.259
[panicked wailing]

598
00:40:30.428 --> 00:40:33.013
[screaming]

599
00:40:39.103 --> 00:40:40.896
[melancholy music continues]

600
00:40:54.368 --> 00:40:56.954
I imagine Ren wanted revenge.

601
00:41:03.919 --> 00:41:05.629
Is he actually…

602
00:41:08.799 --> 00:41:10.718
the Human Vapor. Kyoko?

603
00:41:18.642 --> 00:41:20.352
Or is he possibly…

604
00:41:22.938 --> 00:41:24.732
just a monster with his face?

605
00:41:27.776 --> 00:41:29.945
That can be controlled
by anyone who knows how?

606
00:41:30.446 --> 00:41:32.448
No. I'm telling you. it's him.

607
00:41:34.658 --> 00:41:35.826
Well then.

608
00:41:37.328 --> 00:41:39.455
if Ren is really in there…

609
00:41:48.255 --> 00:41:51.133
was he the kind of person
who would want to kill people?

610
00:41:57.181 --> 00:41:59.642
[sorrowful music playing]

611
00:42:01.268 --> 00:42:03.395
Forgive me if I'm wrong. but I believe…

612
00:42:06.774 --> 00:42:08.859
you're the one who wanted revenge.

613
00:42:19.745 --> 00:42:21.622
The only thing we can do…

614
00:42:25.543 --> 00:42:28.796
is to make sure that we don't forget
those who are gone.

615
00:42:28.879 --> 00:42:31.423
So you're saying
I should just deal with it?

616
00:42:32.424 --> 00:42:34.051
Can you forgive Miura?

617
00:42:36.470 --> 00:42:38.556
After everything that man did.

618
00:42:39.348 --> 00:42:41.976
the suffering he caused you and me.
can you forgive him?

619
00:42:42.059 --> 00:42:43.185
No. I can't.

620
00:42:47.898 --> 00:42:50.442
And that's why
I'll make sure he faces justice.

621
00:43:01.161 --> 00:43:03.163
[music fades out]

622
00:43:04.832 --> 00:43:06.584
[woman 1] Oh my God! Hey!

623
00:43:06.667 --> 00:43:08.919
Hi! Oh. you look amazing!

624
00:43:09.003 --> 00:43:11.005
[indistinct chattering]

625
00:43:27.730 --> 00:43:30.065
[tense music playing]

626
00:43:32.234 --> 00:43:33.068
[gasps]

627
00:43:39.116 --> 00:43:41.535
[sinister music playing]

628
00:43:42.870 --> 00:43:44.538
[Kaho gasping]

629
00:43:47.499 --> 00:43:48.584
[Kaho whimpers]

630
00:43:49.835 --> 00:43:51.962
[footsteps receding]

631
00:44:01.263 --> 00:44:02.681
[Kaho whimpers softly]

632
00:44:02.765 --> 00:44:04.767
[sinister music fades]

633
00:44:29.249 --> 00:44:30.292
Kaho?

634
00:44:33.545 --> 00:44:35.214
Wait. stop. Kyoko!

635
00:44:41.637 --> 00:44:43.639
[eerie music playing]

636
00:45:15.462 --> 00:45:20.008
GO VOTE 11/22
TOKYO GOVERNOR ELECTION

637
00:45:25.597 --> 00:45:30.477
TAKESHI MIURA
CAMPAIGN OFFICE

638
00:45:48.495 --> 00:45:50.497
[eerie music building]

639
00:45:52.708 --> 00:45:54.793
-[booming drumbeat]
-[music fades]

640
00:45:54.877 --> 00:45:57.379
[dramatic music playing]
